						<summary>

						<p>On a pillar setup in the field of Mahadēvappa Kaṇakaṭe.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">12th century A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>This damaged fragmentary record probably intends to state the death of Singiseṭṭi through the Jaina Vow <hi rend="italic">(sallēkhana)</hi> under the guidance of a jaina <hi rend="italic">muni</hi> [Bhadrabāhu ?]. Probably Vardhamāna composed this record.</p>						

						<p>The record is dated Vikramāva, [Vi]ḷambi, Chaitra • dige• It is not certain that Vikrama refers to Chālukya-Vikrama Varsha. The cyclic year Viḷambi occurred twice 1) 1118 A.D., &amp; 2) 1178 during the 12th century A.D.</p>						

						</summary>
